WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:07.490 --> 00:00:14.130
In this video we are going to show you how
to clean the Corona Wires on a brother HL4570CW

00:00:14.130 --> 00:00:16.940
or similar model printer.

00:00:16.940 --> 00:00:20.000
Start by opening the printer cover.

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:24.160
Next, remove the drum toner unit by carefully
sliding it out until it stops.

00:00:24.160 --> 00:00:31.050
This engage the lever lock and remove the
drum toner unit by grasping the two handles

00:00:31.050 --> 00:00:34.530
raising the from of the assembly and lifting
it out of the printer.

00:00:34.530 --> 00:00:47.200
Next, remove all the toner cartridges by pushing
forward on each toner cartridge and lifting

00:00:47.200 --> 00:00:48.610
out of the drum unit.

00:00:48.610 --> 00:00:55.520
Under each toner cartridge, there is a cover
plate.

00:00:55.520 --> 00:01:05.979
One at a time, remove the cover plate to reveal
the Corona Wire and the green tab to the right.

00:01:05.979 --> 00:01:10.720
Press down on the green tab and slide it back
and forth across the unit.

00:01:10.720 --> 00:01:14.890
Repeat this 5-10 times to clean the Corona
Wire.

00:01:14.890 --> 00:01:16.970
Return the tap back to its original position.

00:01:16.970 --> 00:01:23.200
Be sure to slide the tab all the way to right
until you hear the click.

00:01:23.200 --> 00:01:27.200
Snap the cover back into place and repeat
the process for the each of the remaining

00:01:27.200 --> 00:01:29.310
Corona Wire.

00:01:29.310 --> 00:01:41.499
Last position can be a little tight but make
sure the cover is properly snapped back its

00:01:41.499 --> 00:01:49.060
place.

00:01:49.060 --> 00:01:54.520
Reinsert the toner cartridges one at a time
into the drum unit by clicking them back into

00:01:54.520 --> 00:01:55.619
place.

00:01:55.619 --> 00:02:08.910
Return the drum toner unit to the printer
in a reverse matter.

00:02:08.910 --> 00:02:16.960
First, position the unit in the open position
then engaging locking lever.

00:02:16.960 --> 00:02:23.820
Slowly slide the drum toner unit all the way
in until you hear the click.

00:02:23.820 --> 00:02:28.190
Close the cover and the printer is ready to
use.

